

15,01                                Going to Hell

15,01                mmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm
15,01                14,15   15    14I slammed hard on the brakes,          
15,01                14,15   15  14My car lurched, twisted and turned.      
15,01                14,15   15    14But I was going far too fast,          
15,01                14,15   15  14A lesson I never seemed to learn.        
15,01                14,15   15  14My body catapulted straight ahead,       
15,01                14,15  15   14The seat belt cutting me in half,        
15,01                14,15  15   14My skull flew through the window,        
15,01                14,15  15  14On the cold street I lay there dead.      
15,01                14,15  15                                     14       
15,01                14,15   15  14I see my corpse lying very still.        
15,01                14,15  15    14The blood oozes from my heart.          
15,01                14,15  15  14The damage is much too bad to cure,       
15,01                14,15  15     14My physical being torn apart.          
15,01                14,15   15 14I start to drift toward a far light,      
15,01                14,15  15   14Shining, blinding, much too bright.      
15,01                14,15  15     14I hear a voice booming aloud...        
15,01                14,15  15   14"Welcome to the rest of your life."      
15,01                14,15  15                                       14     
15,01                14,15  15   14A new beginning, as I am condemned,      
15,01                14,15  15    14To live my life in Satan's lair.        
15,01                14,15  15 14For my evil ways, eternity in despair.     
15,01                14,15  15  14The burning flames consume my soul,       
15,01                14,15   15  14Lonely pain, the demon's so cold.        
15,01                14,15  15     14Searing heat, a bloody goat,           
15,01                15,15 14A wicked laugh from a cut, gurgling throat.  
15,01                15,15 14The horrible torture becomes my only friend, 
15,01                15,15      14Satan's slave until the very end.       
15,01                """"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
